Reasoning: 
1. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper deals with the extension of the notion of level planarity to surfaces different from the plane, which is a topic closely related to computational geometry. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the computational complexity of testing the existence of a level embedding of a level graph on different surfaces, which is a problem related to data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper deals with level graphs, which are a topic in discrete mathematics. 
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper discusses the complexity of testing the simultaneous level planarity of a set of level graphs, which is a problem related to game theory. 
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with the extension of the notion of level planarity to different surfaces, which is a topic that can be applied to social and information networks.
